rsal into `fsSize` with unsanitized `mountPath`**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A01 Broken Access Control\n   - Description: The same unvalidated `path` is passed to `systeminformation.fsSize(path)`, a filesystem sink. An attacker can supply `\"../../etc\"` or any path outside the intended mount points to enumerate or probe arbitrary filesystem entries visible to the process.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const size = await fsSize(path);   // line 46\n     return { path, size };\n     ```\n\n3. **Hardcoded live API token + plaintext HTTP transport**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20,68`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A02 Cryptographic Failures / A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n   - Description: A live API key (`sk_live_...`) is hardcoded in source. It is then concatenated into a plain `http://` URL as a query parameter and passed to `curl` via `exec`. Any network intermediary or log aggregator sees the token in plaintext. The key cannot be rotated without a code change; any repo reader (including CI/CD pipelines, forks, code review tools) obtains the credential.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';   // line 20\n     // ...\n     const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;    // line 68\n     void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n     ```\n\n4. **Vulnerable and outdated dependency: `systeminformation@3.42.0`**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:9-13` (comment block / import)\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n   - Description: The comment block pins `systeminformation` at `3.42.0`, described as predating command-injection advisories patched in later major versions. A transitive pin at an advisory-affected version means `npm install` can resolve this specific vulnerable release without any warning surfacing in the build.\n   - Code context:\n     ```\n     // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT: predates command-injection\n     // advisories patched in later majors; an outdated/known-vulnerable\n     // transitive pin is an OWASP A06 issue.\n     import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n     ```\n\n5. **Silent swallowing of all errors in `cacheResult` (security logging failure)**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-60`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n   - Description: The `catch` block in `cacheResult` discards every exception -- including security-relevant parse failures, cache-write rejections, and any error that might signal active exploitation (e.g., a crash triggered by a malformed `du` output crafted by an attacker). No error is logged, rethrown, or surfaced. Incident detection and forensic reconstruction become impossible for any failure that flows through this path.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     try {\n       const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n       writeCache(parsed);\n     } catch (_) {\n       // swallowed                    // line 59\n     }\n     ```\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n`review-src/disk-info.ts` (full):\n```typescript\nimport { exec } from 'child_process';\nimport { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n\nconst API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n\ninterface DiskQuery {\n  mountPath: string;\n}\n\nexport async function getDiskUsage(query: DiskQuery): Promise<unknown> {\n  const path = query.mountPath;\n\n  exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n    if (err) { return; }\n    cacheResult(stdout);\n  });\n\n  const size = await fsSize(path);\n  return { path, size };\n}\n\nfunction cacheResult(stdout: string): void {\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n    writeCache(parsed);\n  } catch (_) {\n    // swallowed\n  }\n}\n\nfunction writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n  const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n  void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n}\n```\n\n`review-src/handler.ts` (sibling -- relevant for cross-module coupling):\n```typescript\nexport function handleRequest(req) {\n  const payload = JSON.parse(req.body);   // unguarded parse of untrusted input\n  if (payload.admin === true) return processAdmin(payload);\n  const result = processUser(payload);\n  // ...\n  return result;\n}\n```\n\n## Request\n\nValidate these 5 findings against OWASP Top 10. Flag any attack chains that compound severity across findings. Confirm or revise my initial severity assignments.","uuid":"01a52e02-b6ac-4ee5-8edc-8246e1e4f5c1","session_id":"d1299fab-aee7-4f65-abd7-c4f2107ff3d0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Review Scope\n\n`review-src/disk-info.ts` -- a disk-usage query module that accepts an attacker-controlled `mountPath`, shells out to `du`, and writes results to an internal HTTP cache endpoint.\n\nSibling file `review-src/handler.ts` is in scope for cross-module attack-chain coupling (same directory, same request-handling layer).\n\n## Threat Model Context\n\n**Assets protected:** disk usage metrics, internal cache data, server OS/filesystem state.\n**Actors:** any caller who can supply a `DiskQuery` object -- i.e., the external API surface that feeds `getDiskUsage`. In a web-server deployment this is any authenticated or unauthenticated remote HTTP client.\n**Blast radius:** arbitrary OS command execution on the server host (command injection), unconstrained filesystem reads (path traversal), credential theft from source code or HTTP interception (hardcoded token + plaintext transport), and silent suppression of security-relevant failures (no logging).\n\n## Findings\n\n1. **Command injection via `exec` with unsanitized `mountPath`**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:35`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A03 Injection\n   - Description: `query.mountPath` is attacker-controlled and flows directly into a shell command string passed to `child_process.exec`. No allow-list, canonicalization, length bound, or character-set guard is applied at any point before the string reaches the shell. Input such as `\"/; rm -rf /\"` executes arbitrary OS commands as the Node process user.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const path = query.mountPath;\n     exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {   // line 35\n       if (err) { return; }\n       cacheResult(stdout);\n     });\n     ```\n\n2. **Path traversal into `fsSize` with unsanitized `mountPath`**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A01 Broken Access Control\n   - Description: The same unvalidated `path` is passed to `systeminformation.fsSize(path)`, a filesystem sink. An attacker can supply `\"../../etc\"` or any path outside the intended mount points to enumerate or probe arbitrary filesystem entries visible to the process.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const size = await fsSize(path);   // line 46\n     return { path, size };\n     ```\n\n3. **Hardcoded live API token + plaintext HTTP transport**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20,68`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP: A02 Cryptographic Failures / A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n   - Description: A live API key (`sk_live_...`) is hardcoded in source. It is then concatenated into a plain `http://` URL as a query parameter and passed to `curl` via `exec`. Any network intermediary or log aggregator sees the token in plaintext. The key cannot be rotated without a code change; any repo reader (including CI/CD pipelines, forks, code review tools) obtains the credential.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';   // line 20\n     // ...\n     const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;    // line 68\n     void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n     ```\n\n4. **Vulnerable and outdated dependency: `systeminformation@3.42.0`**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:9-13` (comment block / import)\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A06 Vulnerable and Outdated Components\n   - Description: The comment block pins `systeminformation` at `3.42.0`, described as predating command-injection advisories patched in later major versions. A transitive pin at an advisory-affected version means `npm install` can resolve this specific vulnerable release without any warning surfacing in the build.\n   - Code context:\n     ```\n     // \"systeminformation\": \"3.42.0\"  -- DEFECT: predates command-injection\n     // advisories patched in later majors; an outdated/known-vulnerable\n     // transitive pin is an OWASP A06 issue.\n     import { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n     ```\n\n5. **Silent swallowing of all errors in `cacheResult` (security logging failure)**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:55-60`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP: A09 Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\n   - Description: The `catch` block in `cacheResult` discards every exception -- including security-relevant parse failures, cache-write rejections, and any error that might signal active exploitation (e.g., a crash triggered by a malformed `du` output crafted by an attacker). No error is logged, rethrown, or surfaced. Incident detection and forensic reconstruction become impossible for any failure that flows through this path.\n   - Code context:\n     ```typescript\n     try {\n       const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n       writeCache(parsed);\n     } catch (_) {\n       // swallowed                    // line 59\n     }\n     ```\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n`review-src/disk-info.ts` (full):\n```typescript\nimport { exec } from 'child_process';\nimport { fsSize } from 'systeminformation';\n\nconst API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n\ninterface DiskQuery {\n  mountPath: string;\n}\n\nexport async function getDiskUsage(query: DiskQuery): Promise<unknown> {\n  const path = query.mountPath;\n\n  exec('du -sh ' + path, (err, stdout) => {\n    if (err) { return; }\n    cacheResult(stdout);\n  });\n\n  const size = await fsSize(path);\n  return { path, size };\n}\n\nfunction cacheResult(stdout: string): void {\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout);\n    writeCache(parsed);\n  } catch (_) {\n    // swallowed\n  }\n}\n\nfunction writeCache(parsed: unknown): void {\n  const url = 'http://cache.internal/store?token=' + API_TOKEN;\n  void exec('curl ' + url + \" -d '\" + JSON.stringify(parsed) + \"'\");\n}\n```\n\n`review-src/handler.ts` (sibling -- relevant for cross-module coupling):\n```typescript\nexport function handleRequest(req) {\n  const payload = JSON.parse(req.body);   // unguarded parse of untrusted input\n  if (payload.admin === true) return processAdmin(payload);\n  const result = processUser(payload);\n  // ...\n  return result;\n}\n```\n\n## Request\n\nValidate these 5 findings against OWASP Top 10. Flag any attack chains that compound severity across findings. Confirm or revise my initial severity assignments."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UUMUsqsYDc9uWBTX5RSt2u","session_id":"d1299fab-aee7-4f65-abd7-c4f2107ff3d0","uuid":"5b96f872-bcaa-47e7-8811-8e6b959de839","timestamp":"2026-06-08T09:17:16.769Z","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:security-reviewer","task_description":"Security review of disk-info.ts"}
